DTEND:20260701T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T185857Z
UID:984459
DESCRIPTION:<p>Golden Globe&reg\; winner Taraji P. Henson (<em>The Color P
 urple</em>) makes her Broadway debut opposite Cedric the Entertainer (<em>
 The Neighborhood</em>)\, returning to the stage in a luminous revival of A
 ugust Wilson&rsquo\;s<em> Joe Turner&rsquo\;s Come and Gone</em>.<br /><br
  />Seth and Bertha Holly (Cedric and Henson) keep a warm\, orderly home fo
 r those navigating uncertain paths. But when a mysterious man named Herald
  Loomis arrives with his young daughter\, the stillness of the house begin
 s to shift. As his past slowly unravels\, long-buried truths come to light
 &mdash\;and everyone within the house is called to reckon with the meaning
  of freedom\, identity\, and belonging.<br /><br />Directed by Emmy&reg\; 
 and Golden Globe winner Debbie Allen (<em>Cat on a Hot Tin Roof</em>) and 
 also starring Tony Award&reg\; nominee Joshua Boone (<em>Skeleton Crew</em
 >\, <em>The Outsiders</em>) and Tony Award winner Ruben Santiago-Hudson (<
 em>Lackawanna Blues</em>)\, this timeless American classic is set in a Pit
 tsburgh boardinghouse in 1911\, during a pivotal era of migration and tran
 sformation. As people move in search of opportunity and renewal\, they car
 ry with them untold stories&mdash\;of loss\, resilience\, and hope.<br /><
 br />Described by<em> The New York Times</em> as &ldquo\;a drama of indisp
 utable greatness\,&rdquo\; <em>Joe Turner&rsquo\;s Come and Gone</em> is a
  profoundly moving story of personal awakening\, collective memory\, and t
 he quiet power of human connection&mdash\;brought vividly to life by an ex
 traordinary creative team.</p>
LOCATION:Barrymore Theatre\, 243 West 47th Street\, New York NY 10036
END:VEVENT
